<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102371331010861></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102371331010861><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102371331010861>RE: Dex/AC</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102371331010861#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>327 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 10th 8:56 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>DEX, AC and CHA are equally important to a bard.&nbsp;&nbsp;AC because you will draw aggro and you need to survive long enough for the tanks to pull the mob off you.  DEX for the reasons you stated above.  CHA because your charm and mezz songs work better with high CHA.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
