<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102580287557491></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102580287557491><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102580287557491>RE: Bard Pets?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102580287557491#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=173458><span id= >Enharmonee</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 4th 1:25 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It lasts about 18 seconds if i remember right (depending on your CHA), and even if you do keep playing it it will break; even so, charm kiting is one of the best ways for bards to lvl at 27-...o maybe around 35ish?&nbsp;&nbsp;You charm a mob (preferably even or yellow) then have it attack another mob (weaker than your pet, but no less than dark blue), while they beat the daylights out of each other, you stand by twisting selos and healing if you want.  When charm breaks, run and re-sing the charm song to your original pet, and repeat the above.  If your pet is gettin really low on health, and the other mob still has a pretty good amount of health left, (and your willing to take a few hits), next time charm breaks, charm the mob with more health, and just go melee your original pet (the new pet wont take agro from your original, the original is still really P.O.'d that you charmed him, so you might as well get a few hits in as long as your takin em).  Only thing wrong with this is it gets really repetitive and a little boring.  What I did was charm kite till 30, go to OT for about 4 more lvls, then charm kite again until 38.  Keep in mind the lvl 27 charm song only works on mobs 39 and under.  You do get a stronger charm song (i think mobs 55 and under) at...i think its lvl 39, but it takes mana.  Hope this helped!<br>&nbsp;<br>Enharmonee SongRider<br>Bard of the 40th Broken String<br>Legacy of the Dragoons</td></tr>
