<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102185026237450></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102185026237450><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102185026237450>My advice for soloing...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102185026237450#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=164420><span id= >Fyla</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 19th 7:26 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Im currently 51 so im starting to get to the point where i can not effectivly solo, but heres what i did when i did choose to solo.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are 4 ways of kiting that i found effective, listed in order of lvl where you can start<br>AE DoT kiting: 18<br>Fear kiting: 26<br>Charm kiting: 27, though far more effective at 39<br>Chant kiting: feasible at 38, much better at 49<br>AE DoT kiting: starting at lvl 18 you get your second AE DoT, go to Loio, even though the zone sucks, pull about 10 mobs, and start twisting selos, DDD, and CoD, do so until everything is dead and you've lvled or until you get bored, these songs actually have a minimum range so you need to time your turns very carefully, also be sure to have selos up at all times.<br>Fear kiting: this is alot of fun since it keeps your melee skills up.  Snare with the lvl 23 song, and fear, careful not to fear NPCs and what not.  Just hack away at they're backs, if your getting near an add, just run away, and snare/fear again, i've actually fear kited the lord room in Lguk like this, great even at higher lvls.<br>Charm kiting: IMO the most effective form of kiting, many inexperienced bards get killed because they are foolish about this.  I started this in FM with giants but it works anywhere, even in dungeons. Pull several mobs, 3 is ideal, then charm one, STAY ON THAT TARGET, stand still and let the others hit you then back off, they will engage your pet, when the pet is near death, charm another, snare the hurt one and tell the new pet to kill that while running in circles, repeat and so forth for great xp, careful about mana at 39+<br>Chant kiting: boring but effective, run in circles with dots, works well with sow so you can use 30/38/46 songs, or with the long duration selos at 49, was able to chant kite quag maelstrom in 5 minutes like this.<br>GL bards<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
